{
  "texts": [
    "In humans, each individual in a care-based relationship is normatively expected to meet the other's needs (i.e., significant welfare interests) to the best of their respective abilities (for qualifications, see [11,45]).",
    "But in most current theories, AI-powered systems do not have welfare interests or needs.",
    "How will this affect human expectations about appropriate behavior with an AI friend or companion?",
    "Or consider the transaction function.",
    "This involves keeping track of benefits given or received to ensure fair and proportional treatment [11,45]."
  ]
}